{{Infobox school |image = |name = Al Dhafra Private School |motto = |type = Private profit-making K-12 school |established = 1989 |city = [[Al Ain]] |country = [[United Arab Emirates]] |principal = Roger McDuff |staff = Ove 100 |grades = Nursery to Year 12 |enrollment_as_of = as of September 2009 |enrollment = Approximately 2700 |campus = Urban |imagesize = 170px |religious_affiliation = Independent |website = {{URL|http://www.dhafra-alain.sch.ae/}} |lastupdate= 18 November 2009 }}
'''Al Dhafra Private Schools''' are private educational institutions located in the Al Manaseer area of [[Al Ain]] and in [[Mohammed Bin Zayed City, Shabiya 9]] in the [[Emirate of Abu Dhabi]], [[United Arab Emirates]]. The schools are a [[Cambridge International Examinations]] Center, a CITA ([[Commission on International and Trans-Regional Accreditation]], USA) candidate schools and is registered with the [[United Arab Emirates Ministry of Education]].
The schools have more than 2700 students of over 27 nationalities.<ref>[http://www.dubaifaqs.com/al-dhafra-private-school-al-ain.php Al Dhafra Private School]. Dubai Facts.</ref> It was established in 1989.
