{{Infobox university | name = Catholic University of Zimbabwe | image = | image_size = | image_alt = | caption = | motto = ''Pro Deo et Sapientia'' ([[Latin]]) | motto_lang = Latin | mottoeng ="For God and wisdom" | established = {{start date|1999}} | closed = <!-- {{end date|YYYY}} --> | type = [[Private university|Private]] | parent =Zimbabwe Catholic Bishops Conference (ZCBC) | affiliation = | academic_affiliation =[[Zimbabwe Council of Higher Education]] (ZIMCHE) | endowment = | budget = | rector =Professor Ranga Zinyemba | officer_in_charge = | chairman = | chairperson = | chancellor = Archbishop of Harare Diocese [[Robert Ndlovu]] | president = | vice-president = | superintendent = | provost = | vice_chancellor=Professor Ranga Zinyemba | principal = | dean = | director = | academic_staff = | administrative_staff = | students = | undergrad = | postgrad = | doctoral = | other = | city = [[Harare]] | province = [[Harare Metropolitan Province]] | country = [[Zimbabwe]] | campus =St. Augustine (Bulawayo), Diocesan Training Centre (Mutare), Hope Tariro School (Chinhoyi) | language = | free_label = | free = | colours =Gold and maroon | website = {{URL|www.cuz.ac.zw}} | logo = | footnotes = | founder = Archbishop of Harare Diocese Robert Christopher Ndlovu, Professor George P. Kahari, Herbert Munangatire | religious_affiliation = [[Roman Catholic Church]] | coor = {{coord|-17.868876|31.06737|display=it}} | logo_size = | logo_alt = }}
The '''Catholic University of Zimbabwe''' ('''CUZ''') is a [[Catholic Church]] affiliated university<ref name="zd2015">{{cite news|url=https://www.thezimbabwedaily.com/news/28246-eighty-nine-students-graduate-from-the-catholic-university-of-zimbabwe.html |title=Eighty nine students graduate from the Catholic University of Zimbabwe |newspaper=The Zimbabwe Daily |date=25 April 2015}}</ref> established in 1999 in [[Harare]], [[Zimbabwe]]'s capital city. It offers six undergraduate degree programs: Bachelor of Business Management & Information Technology (Honors), Bachelor of Business Management (Honors), Bachelor of Accounting (Honors), Bachelor of Social Science in Development Studies (Honors), Bachelor of Theology and Bachelor of Arts Dual (Honours). It also offers a variety of short courses under the Faculty of Commerce and the Faculty of Humanities.
In 2014, the university extended its reach by opening three satellite campuses in [[Bulawayo]], [[Chinhoyi]] and [[Mutare]].
The Catholic University plans to introduce more full-time degree programs and short courses in response to students' needs.{{Citation needed|date=July 2018}}
