The '''Faroese Teachers' Association''' ({{lang-fo|Føroya Lærarafelag}}) is a trade union for educators in the [[Faroe Islands]]. The association was established in 1898,<ref>Bjørg Jacobsen et al. 2011. ''Konubrot: heiđursrit til Elin Súsonnu Jacobsen''. Tórshavn: Fróðskapur / Faroe University Press, p. 37.</ref><ref name="Sigurdardottir">Sigurðardóttir, Turið. 2009. Translation in Faroese Children's Literature. In: B. J. Epstein (ed.), ''Northern Lights: Translation in the Nordic Countries'', pp. 181–190. Oxford: Peter Lang, p. 185.</ref> and its press, Bókadeild Føroya Lærarafelags (Faroese Teachers' Association Publishing Company), was established in 1956.<ref name="Sigurdardottir"/><ref>[http://www.bfl.fo/Vis-tidindi.aspx?ID=881&Action=1&NewsId=4288&M=NewsV2&PID=2878#.VxWjrjB96hc Bókadeild Føroya Lærarafelags.]</ref><ref>Thomsen, Niels Jákup, et al. 2014. ''Rights Catalogue''. Tórshavn: Bókadeild Føroya Lærarafelags, p. 3.</ref>
