{{short description|New Zealand free-diver}} '''Kate Middleton''' (born December 23, 1987 in [[Canada]]) is the current [[New Zealand]] record holder in the [[Free immersion apnea|free immersion]] discipline (FIM)<ref>{{cite web|url=http://onebreathjamboree.com/2013/11/12/last-day-of-the-one-breath-jamboree/ |title=Archived copy |accessdate=2014-08-14 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140812205458/http://onebreathjamboree.com/2013/11/12/last-day-of-the-one-breath-jamboree/ |archivedate=2014-08-12 |df= }}</ref> and [[Constant weight apnea|constant weight with fins]] (CWT).<ref>{{cite web|author=Stephan Whelan |url=http://www.deeperblue.com/national-records-fall-second-day-one-breath-jamboree-competition/ |title=More National Records Fall During Second Day of One Breath Jamboree Competition – |website=Deeperblue.com |date=2013-11-03 |accessdate=2017-04-19}}</ref> She is the 3rd deepest woman in the world and Vice World Champion Freediver. She owns a Yoga and Freediving resort in Gili Trawangan, Indonesia where she trains and teaches.
