'''F. Sue Chandler''', known as '''Sue (or Suzanne) Chandler''', is a British schoolteacher and textbook writer, who, together with co-author Linda Bostock, wrote the "Bostock and Chandler" series of [[textbook]]s for [[advanced level mathematics]] in the [[United Kingdom|UK]]. At the time she began the series, she was a full-time mathematics teacher at [[Southgate Technical College]] in [[Southgate, London]]. She eventually stopped teaching courses and focused on textbook writing. Her books have sold more than 5 million copies.<ref>{{citation
